  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>The Sport Hotel Barisetti is on a half-board basis. Drinks are not included, there is a charge for water.</p>
<p>Each morning you can enjoy a great spread of continental items from the buffet, many of which are freshly prepared in the kitchen. You'll also find daily hot options including items such as eggs and bacon. Evening meals at the hotel consist of four courses, each with several options to choose from. Dishes are a mix of both Tyrolean and international dishes. </p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>It's easy to see why so many people go back to Sport Hotel Barisetti year after year. The staff are incredibly welcoming and you’re instantly made to feel at home. The location’s fantastic with some of the best mountain views in town. The main shopping street of <a data-udi="umb://document/2dcb1a3292da421780aa165d449493a9" href="/{localLink:umb://document/2dcb1a3292da421780aa165d449493a9}" title="Cortina D’Ampezzo">Cortina</a> is 600 metres away and the Tofana cable car is just 50 metres from the hotel's door.</p>
<h2>Great location</h2>
<p>Start your day by heading up the Tofana cable car, which is just 50 metres from the hotel's door, and take on the slopes where the <span>Ski World Cup and the 2021 World Ski Championships usually takes place. The lower ski area in Tofana is great for warming up, and for those just starting out while the higher slope</span> including the Forcella Rossa are perfect for the more advanced. From this area you can also head over towards the 5 Torri - a must do for any guests staying in the Dolomites. If you want to explore the picturesque Faloria-Cristallo ski area, there is a handy shuttle bus that'll take you there. The Faloria-Cristallo area is<span> famous for hosting the giant slalom during Cortina’s 1956 Winter Olympics, however there are some lovely red and black runs for the less adventurous.</span></p>
<h2>Relax and unwind</h2>
<p>There’s plenty going on in the evenings in Cortina if you fancy venturing out, its about a five minutes walk to the centre where you can find a range of high-end boutiques, cosy cafes and bars. We love spending time in the hotel’s own bar though, chatting about our day with the friendly staff with an Aperol in hand. And If you have time, the hotel has a small wellness area with a sauna and Turkish bath.</p>
<h3>Exclusive to Inghams</h3>
<p>As a ski specialist tour operator we carefully select the very best accommodation in our resorts and package them with flights and transfers, so that you can make the most of your holiday. We have an exclusive agreement with Sport Hotel Barisetti the only UK tour operator to package and sell holidays here - all the more reason to book with Inghams today!</p>]]></description>
